.TH ENV 1 "April, 2026"

.SH NAME
\fBenv\fP \- Print or set environment

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBenv\fP [\fIname\fP=\fIvalue\fP]...
.br
\fBenv\fP [\fIname\fP=\fIvalue\fP]... \fIcmd\fP [\fIargs\fP]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBenv\fP will read arguments containing "=" and add them to the environment.
If an argument without a "=" is found, \fBenv\fP will execute it as a command,
passing the remaining arguments.
.PP
If no arguments are given, or only arguments with "=" are provided, \fBenv\fP
will print the values of all environment variables.

.SH NOTES
Adding variables to the environment with \fBenv\fP does not affect the parent
process that called \fBenv\fP.

.SH BUGS
This \fBenv\fP always returns 0. It should probably return 1 if
.IR execvp (3)
fails.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR environ (7),
.BR putenv (3),
.BR execvp (3)
